label: developmental delay with short stature, dysmorphic facial features, and sparse hair 2
definition: Any developmental delay with short stature, dysmorphic facial features, and sparse hair in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the DPH2 gene.

label: CTNNA1-related diffuse gastric and lobular breast cancer syndrome
definition: Germline pathogenic or likely pathogenic variants in the CTNNA1 gene predispose to hereditary diffuse gastric cancer and lobular breast cancer, a cancer susceptibility syndrome inherited in an autosomal dominant pattern.

label: POLE-related polyposis and colorectal cancer syndrome
definition: An autosomal dominant hereditary syndrome caused by germline pathogenic POLE variants. It is characterized by the presence of colorectal polyps and colorectal cancer.

label: Carey-Fineman-Ziter syndrome 2
definition: Any Carey-Fineman-Ziter syndrome in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the MYMX gene.

label: PAX5-related B lymphopenia and autism spectrum disorder
definition: PAX5 deficiency causing neurodevelopmental abnormalities including autism spectrum disorder in addition to hypogammaglobulinemia due to early B cell developmental block and impaired immune responses.

label: hereditary capillary infantile hemangioma
definition: An instance of capillary infantine hemangioma that is caused by an inherited genomic modification in an individual.

label: hemangioma, capillary infantile, susceptibility to
definition: An inherited susceptibility or predisposition to developing capillary infantile hemangioma.

label: LADD syndrome 1
definition: Any LADD syndrome in which the cause of the disease is a variation in the FGFR2 gene.

label: ichthyosis, annular epidermolytic 1
definition: Any annular epidermolytic ichthiosis in which the cause of the disease is a variation in the KRT10 gene.

label: focal segmental glomerulosclerosis
definition: A renal disorder characterized by sclerotic lesions in the glomeruli. Causes include drugs, viruses, and malignancies (lymphomas), or it may be idiopathic. It presents with asymptomatic proteinuria or nephritic syndrome and it may lead to renal failure.

label: GYG1-related disorder of glycogen metabolism
definition: Any disorder of glycogen metabolism in which the cause of disease is a mutation in the GYG1 gene.

label: deficiency of adenosine deaminase 2
definition: Any disease or disorder in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the ADA2 gene.

label: inherited pseudohypoaldosteronism
definition: A form of pseudohypoaldosteronism that is characterized Mendelian (autosomal dominant, recessive, or X-linked) or chromosomal etiology.

label: primary focal segmental glomerulosclerosis
definition: A form of focal segmental glomerulosclerosis without identifiable etiology. Primary (idiopathic) FSGS has been associated with the presence of circulating permeability factors/cytokines, which cause foot process effacement and proteinuria.

label: PSAP-related sphingolipidosis
definition: A sphingolipidosis caused by variants in the PSAP gene. Clinical and biochemical features vary based on the location of variants within the gene and their molecular impact.

label: hereditary attention deficit-hyperactivity disorder
definition: An instance of attention deficit-hyperactivity disorder that is caused by an inherited genomic modification in an individual.

label: disease related to transplantation
definition: Disease that occurs as a consequence of immunosuppression in a recipient of a solid organ or bone marrow transplant, or as a consequence of the transplantation.

label: disease related to solid organ transplantation
definition: Disease that occurs as a consequence of immunosuppression in a recipient of a solid organ transplant, or as a consequence of the transplantation.

label: disease related to hematopoietic stem cell transplant
definition: Disease that occurs as a consequence of immunosuppression in a recipient of a hematopoietic stem cell transplant, or as a consequence of the transplantation.

label: hereditary skeletal muscle disorder
definition: An instance of muscle tissue disorder that is caused by an inherited genomic modification in an individual.

label: hereditary gallbladder disorder
definition: An instance of gallbladder disorder that is caused by an inherited genomic modification in an individual.

label: food allergy
definition: Gastrointestinal disturbances, skin eruptions, or shock due to allergic reactions to allergens in food.

label: breast implant-associated anaplastic large cell lymphoma
malignant adenoma
definition: A cell type cancer that is composed of epithelial tissue in which tumor cells form glands or glandlike structures, representing an early form of colorectal cancer.

label: epididymis disease
definition: A male reproductive system disease that is located in the epididymis.

label: gastroesophageal cancer
definition: A gastrointestinal system cancer that is located in the proximal esophagus and the distal stomach.

label: nephroma
definition: A kidney benign neoplasm that is located in the kidney cortex.

label: lymph node carcinoma
definition: A lymph node cancer that has material basis in abnormally proliferating cells derives from epithelial cells.

label: auditory system benign neoplasm
definition: A sensory system benign neoplasm that is located in the auditory system.

label: B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma MLL rearranged
definition: A B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma that is characterized by the presence of lymphoblasts that carry a translocation between the KMT2A gene at 11q23.3 and another gene partner resulting in the production of a KMT2A related fusion protein.

label: B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma with ETV6-RUNX1
definition: A B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma that is characterized by the presence of lymphoblasts that carry a translocation between the TEL gene on chromosome 12 and the AML1 gene on chromosome 21, (p13.2;q22.1). It results in the production of the TEL-AML1 (ETV6-RUNX1) fusion protein.

label: B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma with IL3-IGH
definition: A B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma that is characterized by the presence of lymphoblasts that carry a translocation between the IL3 gene on chromosome 5 and the IGH locus on chromosome 14, (q31.1;q32.3).

label: B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma, BCR-ABL1–like
definition: A B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma that has a gene expression profile similar to that of B-ALL with t(9;22)(q34.1;q11.2) BCR-ABL1, but lacks that gene fusion.

label: B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma with IAMP21
definition: A B-lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma that is characterized by amplification of a portion of chromosome 21.

label: NK cell deficiency
definition: A primary immunodeficiency disease that results from defeciency in the number or function of CD56+CD3− NK cell in peripheral blood.

label: T cell and NK cell immunodeficiency
definition: A primary immunodeficiency disease that involves multiple components of the immune system, including both T cell and NK cell immunodeficiency.

label: Libman-Sacks endocarditis
definition: An endocarditis that is characterized by Libman-Sacks vegetations, is common in patients with systemic lupus erythematosus and is commonly complicated with embolic cerebrovascular disease.

label: salivary gland mucinous adenocarcinoma
definition: A salivary gland carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of large pools of extracellular mucin in which clusters of malignant epithelial cells are found.

label: mammary analogue secretory carcinoma
definition: A salivary gland carcinoma that has material basis in a chromosomal translocation that results in an ETV6-NTRK3 fusion gene.

label: subjective cognitive decline
definition: A cognitive disorder that is characterized by the presence of significant and persistent cognitive complaints.

label: acquired laryngomalacia
definition: A laryngeal disease that is characterized by acquired collapse of laryngeal suprastructures.

label: spinal ependymoma, MYCN-amplified
definition: A spinal cord ependymoma that is characterized by MYCN amplification.

label: lung pleomorphic carcinoma
definition: A pleomorphic carcinoma that is characterized by the presence of malignant glandular or squamous cells associated with malignant giant and spindle cells and that is located in the lung.

label: bladder sarcomatoid transitional cell carcinoma
definition: A sarcomatoid transitional cell carcinoma that is located in the bladder.

label: bladder small cell carcinoma
definition: A bladder carcinoma that is characterized as an undifferentiated neoplasm composed of primitive-appearing cells.

label: nonobstructive coronary artery disease
definition: A coronary artery disease that is characterized by atherosclerotic plaque that would not be expected to obstruct blood flow or result in anginal symptoms and stenosis of coronary artery less than 50 percent.

label: childhood supratentorial embryonal tumor with multilayered rosettes, C19MC-altered
definition: A childhood embryonal tumor with multilayered rosettes, C19MC-altered that arises from the supratentorial brain and occurs in children.

label: high-grade B-cell lymphoma double-hit/triple-hit
definition: A B-cell lymphoma that is characterized by the abnormal rearrangement of two genes, MYC gene and either BCL2 or BCL6 genes.

label: benign peritoneal solitary fibrous tumor
definition: A peritoneal benign neoplasm that is characterized by the presence of prominent hemangiopericytoma-like vessels.

label: primary cutaneous gamma-delta t-cell lymphoma
definition: A primary cutaneous T-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma that is characterised by the clonal cutaneous proliferation of activated mature gamma-delta T cells with a cytotoxic phenotype.

label: neurobehavioral disorder with prenatal alcohol exposure
definition: A fetal alcohol spectrum disorder that is characterized by one or more deficits in neurocognition and in self-regulation plus two or more deficits in adaptive functioning, with at least 1 in communication or social communication and interaction.

label: inclusion body myopathy and brain white matter abnormalities
tetrahydrobiopterin (BH4)-deficient hyperphenylalaninemia
definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder that are characterized phenotypically by hyperphenylalaninemia, depletion of the neurotransmitters dopamine and serotonin, and progressive cognitive and motor deficits and that has material basis in autosomal recessive mutations in the genes encoding enzymes involved in the synthesis or regeneration of BH4.

label: dendritic cell deficiency
definition: A primary immunodeficiency disease characterized by impaired function or reduced numbers of dendritic cells.

label: KINSSHIP syndrome
definition: A syndrome characterized by developmental delay, impaired intellectual development, seizures, mesomelic dysplasia, dysmorphic facial features, horseshoe or hypoplastic kidney, and failure to thrive that has material basis in heterozygous mutation in AFF3 on chromosome 2q11.2.

label: Bartholin's gland disease
definition: A female reproductive system disease that is located in Bartholin's gland.
